# Yarn Weights

*Yarn comes in different thicknesses or `"weights"`. These are semi-standardized throughout the world and most commerical yarns will have a symbol on the label denoting the weight.*

![yarn-weights-symbols.png](data:image/png;base64,)

*I do intend to add wraps per inch to the data at a later date so that yarns without labels are not omitted from this database*

---

## VALUES

| KEY | TYPE |
| --- | --- |
| id | interger |
| weightNumber | interger |
| weightName | string with a limit of 25 characters |
|

---

## RETREIVE 

### Request All

```http
GET /api/yarnweights
```

### Request One

```http
GET /api/yarnweights/:id
```

### Response

*Request all will return an array of the objects like the one shown in the template shown below. Request one will return a single object.*

```json
{
	"id": 1,
	"weightNumber": 0,
	"weightName": "lace"
}
```

---

Because this endpoint is intended to be static `CREATE`, `UPDATE`, and `DELETE` are **_not_** available actions.
